d%20Atmospheric%20Administration%20(NOAA)%20and%20US%20Geological%20Survey%20(USGS).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe've%20been%20teetering%20on%20drought%2C%20extreme%20drought%20since%20last%20fall%2C%26quot%3B%20Colin%20Wellenkamp%2C%20the%20executive%20director%20of%20the%20Mississippi%20River%20Cities%20and%20Towns%20Initiative%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fedition.cnn.com%2F2023%2F09%2F21%2Fus%2Fmississippi-low-water-levels-drought-climate%2Findex.html%5C%22%3Etold%20%3Cem%3ECNN%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20get%20a%20little%20reprieve%2C%20and%20then%20it's%20warm%20and%20dry.%20We%20really%20haven't%20ever%20totally%20climbed%20out%20of%20the%20drought%20from%20last%20fall%20for%20the%20whole%20river%20yet%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20further%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20exceptional%20drought%20comes%20at%20a%20time%20when%20Louisiana%20and%20Mississippi%20experienced%20their%20hottest%20year%20on%20record%2C%20according%20to%20NOAA%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20Midwest%20has%20been%20experiencing%20extraordinarily%20high%20temperature%20due%20to%20which%20structures%20that%20are%20normally%20accessible%20by%20boat%20can%20be%20reached%20on%20foot.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWater%20level%20at%20one%20of%20the%20gauges%20was%20near%20zero%20on%20September%2020%2C%20with%20no%20improvement%20expected%20in%20coming%20days%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3ECNN%3C%2Fem%3E%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%20similar%20situation%20had%20occurred%20in%20October%20last%20year%20when%20tourists%20walked%20up%20to%20Tower%20Rock%2C%20one%20of%20the%20popular%20tourists%20spots%20in%20the%20river.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPrevious%20to%20last%20year%2C%20it%20was%20probably%20only%20accessible%20once%20or%20twice%20in%20the%20last%20decade%2C%26quot%3B%20Steve%20Schell%2C%20a%20natural%20history%20biologist%20at%20the%20Missouri%20Department%20of%20Conservation%2C%20told%20%3Cem%3ECNN%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAmerican%20space%20agency%20NASA%20said%20Earth%20experienced%20its%20hottest%20summer%20on%20record%20this%20year%20with%20temperature%20in%20the%20months%20of%20June%2C%20July%2C%20and%20August%200.23%20degrees%20Celsius%20higher%20than%20any%20previous%20summer.%20This%20was%201.2%20degrees%20Celsius%20warmer%20than%20the%20average%20summer%20between%201951%20and%201980%2C%20NASA%20further%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EGreenhouse%20gas%20emissions%20have%20been%20identified%20as%20a%20major%20driver%20behind%20climate%20change%20and%20the%20worldwide%20warming%20trend%20that%20resulted%20in%20such%20a%20sweltering%20summer.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20tropical%20Pacific%20Ocean%20also%20experienced%20El%20Nino%2C%20a%20natural%20climate%20trend%20characterised%20by%20higher-than-normal%20sea%20surface%20temperatures.%20The%20phenomenon%20may%20have%20wide-ranging%20consequences%2C%20frequently%20bringing%20colder%2C%20wetter%20weather%20to%20the%20Southwest%20of%20the%20US%20and%20drought%20to%20nations%20in%20the%20western%20Pacific%2C%20such%20as%20Australia%20and%20Indonesia%2C%20according%20to%20NASA.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695381540000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-09%2Frb0gtar8_dry-mississippi-river-1200_625x300_22_September_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fwater-level-in-mississippi-river-plummets-for-second-consecutive-year-4414199%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22An%20area%20of%20400%20miles%20is%20at%20low%20water%20threshold%2C%20as%20per%20National%20Oceanic%20and%20Atmospheric%20Administration%20(NOAA)%20and%20US%20Geological%20Survey%20(USGS).%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fwater-level-in-mississippi-river-plummets-for-second-consecutive-year-4414199%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fwater-level-in-mississippi-river-plummets-for-second-consecutive-year-4414199