20not%20making%20the%20reports%20on%20the%20Joshimath%20subsidence%20public.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20see%20no%20reason%20that%20the%20state%20should%20keep%20the%20reports%20prepared%20by%20the%20experts%20secret%20and%20not%20disclose%20the%20same%20to%20the%20public%20at%20large%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20bench%20comprising%20Chief%20Justice%20Vipin%20Sanghi%20and%20Justice%20Alok%20Kumar%20Verma%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fdehradun%2Fjoshimath-sinking-no-reason-to-keep-reports-by-experts-secret-says-uttarakhand-high-court%2Farticleshow%2F103851241.cms%5C%22%3Esaid%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Cem%3ETimes%20of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20further%20said%3A%20%E2%80%9CIn%20fact%2C%20circulation%20of%20the%20said%20reports%20would%20provide%20vital%20information%20to%20the%20public%2C%20and%20the%20public%20would%20have%20confidence%20in%20them%20that%20the%20state%20is%20serious%20about%20dealing%20with%20the%20situation.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20made%20these%20remarks%20when%20reports%20prepared%20by%20eight%20Union%20government%20institutes%20tasked%20to%20study%20Joshimath%E2%80%99s%20subsidence%20were%20placed%20in%20a%20sealed%20cover.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20January%20this%20year%2C%20the%20high%20court%2C%20upon%20reviewing%20a%20petition%2C%20had%20directed%20the%20state%20government%20to%20involve%20certain%20experts%20in%20the%20study%20of%20Joshimath%E2%80%99s%20subsidence.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20it%20found%20that%20even%20after%20eight%20months%2C%20the%20government%20had%20not%20complied%20with%20its%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EUttarakhand%E2%80%99s%20Joshimath%20town%20has%20a%20history%20of%20experiencing%20subsidence%20(the%20sinking%20of%20its%20land)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fworld-asia-india-64201536%5C%22%3Edue%20to%20a%20combination%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20having%20been%20built%20on%20weak%20land%20and%20being%20a%20construction%20hub.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOver%20300%20families%20in%20Joshimath%20were%20displaced%20in%20January%20this%20year%20after%20subsidence%20caused%20cracks%20to%20appear%20in%20hundreds%20of%20buildings.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fdehradun%2Futtarakhand-govt-on-joshimath-probing-ntpc-project-role%2Farticleshow%2F96976575.cms%5C%22%3ESoon%20after%20the%20cracks%20were%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20eight%20Union%20government%20institutes%20began%20analysing%20the%20reasons%20for%20the%20town%E2%80%99s%20land%20subsidence.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fjoshimath-himalayas-explainer-warnings-reports-construction-ntpc%5C%22%3EUncontrolled%20Construction%2C%20Ignored%20Warnings%3A%20How%20Joshimath%20Sank%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20newspaper%20also%20reported%20that%20it%20had%20accessed%20the%20eight%20institutes%E2%80%99%20reports.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20said%20that%20the%20Central%20Building%20Research%20Institute%2C%20the%20nodal%20agency%20among%20the%20eight%20institutes%2C%20had%20found%20that%20out%20of%202%2C364%20houses%20it%20analysed%20in%20Joshimath%2C%2020%25%20were%20%E2%80%98unusable%E2%80%99%2C%2042%25%20needed%20%E2%80%98further%20assessment%E2%80%99%2C%2020%25%20were%20%E2%80%98usable%E2%80%99%20and%201%25%20needed%20to%20be%20%E2%80%98demolished%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20was%20hearing%20a%20recall%20application%20by%20the%20state%20government%20over%20the%20chief%20secretary%E2%80%99s%20personal%20appearance.%20During%20the%20hearing%2C%20the%20petitioner%E2%80%99s%20counsel%2C%20Snigdha%20Tiwari%2C%20pointed%20out%20that%20the%20reports%20were%20placed%20in%20a%20sealed%20cover.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695370522000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F22130725%2FUttarakhand-high-court-2.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fno-reason-for-joshimath-reports-to-be-kept-secret-saysuttarakhand-high-court%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20court%20made%20these%20remarks%20when%20reports%20prepared%20by%20eight%20Union%20government%20institutes%20tasked%20to%20study%20Joshimath's%20subsidence%20were%20placed%20in%20a%20sealed%20cover.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fno-reason-for-joshimath-reports-to-be-kept-secret-saysuttarakhand-high-court%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20Sanatan%20Dharma%2C%20Bharat%20And%20The%20Indian%20Constitution%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20Constitution%20of%20any%20nation%20embodies%20its%20collective%20values%2C%20aspirations%2C%20and%20provides%20a%20roadmap%20for%20achieving%20these%20goals.%20It%20also%20delineates%20the%20authority%20vested%20in%20the%20government%20and%20how%20it%20should%20be%20exercised%20to%20realise%20these%20values.%20In%20the%20case%20of%20India%2C%20its%20Constitution%20draws%20heavily%20from%20the%20rich%20tapestry%20of%20civilisational%20values%20cultivated%20over%20millennia%2C%20particularly%20those%20rooted%20in%20the%20Sanatan%20Dharma.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESanatan%20Dharma%20represents%20the%20eternal%2C%20timeless%20and%20unchanging%20traditions%20that%20have%20evolved%20in%20the%20landmass%20of%20%3Cem%3EBharat-Khanda%3C%2Fem%3E%20(the%20Indian%20subcontinent).%20These%20traditions%20are%20so%20assimilated%20in%20this%20culture%20that%2C%20the%20culture%20that%20blossomed%2C%20flourished%20and%20evolved%20on%20this%20geographical%20entity%20came%20to%20be%20known%20as%20Sanatan%20Dharam.%20It%20is%20not%20a%20religion%20like%20Abrahimcal%20religion%20but%20a%20way%20of%20life.%20The%20basis%20of%20this%20Dharma%20is%20Hinduism%2C%20though%20other%20streams%20like%20Buddhism%20and%20Jainism%20also%20added%20their%20valuable%20contributions.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20fundamental%20values%20enshrined%20in%20the%20Indian%20Constitution%20include%20liberty%2C%20equality%2C%20fraternity%2C%20peaceful%20coexistence%2C%20democracy%2C%20and%20respect%20for%20nature%20and%20all%20living%20beings.%20These%20values%20have%20deep%20ties%20to%20Hindu%20culture%2C%20one%20of%20the%20world's%20oldest%20and%20most%20enduring%20civilisations.%20This%20article%20explores%20how%20Hinduism's%20core%20principles%20have%20significantly%20contributed%20to%20the%20foundational%20structure%20of%20the%20Indian%20Constitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20very%20name%20of%20Bharat%20is%20traced%20to%20the%20Sanatan%20Dharma.%20The%20Indian%20Constitution%20begins%20with%20the%20declaration%20in%20Article%201(1)%2C%20%26quot%3BIndia%2C%20that%20is%20Bharat%2C%20shall%20be%20a%20Union%20of%20States.%26quot%3B%20The%20choice%20of%20the%20name%20%26quot%3BBharat%26quot%3B%20goes%20back%20to%20India's%20pre-Muslim%20and%20pre-British%20history%2C%20drawing%20from%20the%20legends%20of%20ancient%20Hindu%20traditions.%20The%20term%20'Bharat'%20is%20intertwined%20with%20the%20country's%20ancient%20identity%2C%20with%20references%20dating%20back%20to%20the%20Mahabharata%20era.%20This%20was%20a%20time%20when%20Bharata%2C%20a%20legendary%20emperor%2C%20united%20the%20Indian%20subcontinent%20into%20a%20single%20political%20entity%20known%20as%3Cem%3E%20%26quot%3BBharatvarsha.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%20Thus%2C%20the%20very%20name%20'Bharat'%20reflects%20India's%20deep-rooted%20connection%20to%20Hindu%20heritage.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EUnity%20in%20Diversity%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20phrase%20%26quot%3BUnion%20of%20States%26quot%3B%20signifies%20the%20cultural%20and%20historical%20fact%20that%20India's%20foundation%20has%20always%20been%20a%20diverse%2C%20pluralistic%2C%20and%20tolerant%20society%20where%20numerous%20sub-cultures%20coexisted%20and%20thrived.%20Many%20of%20these%20sub-cultures%20either%20originated%20from%20Hinduism%20or%20were%20significantly%20influenced%20by%20it.%20Despite%20the%20presence%20of%20diverse%20micro-cultures%2C%20there%20has%20always%20been%20an%20underlying%20political%2C%20geographical%2C%20and%20cultural%20unity%20in%20India%2C%20guided%20by%20the%20cultural%20tenets%20of%20Hinduism.%20This%20unity%20has%20periodically%20manifested%20as%20centralised%20power%20while%20allowing%20ample%20space%20for%20regional%20sub-cultures%20to%20flourish%2C%20evolve%2C%20and%20endure.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Indian%20Constitution%2C%20in%20Part%20IV%20A%2C%20Article%2051-A%2C%20outlines%20Fundamental%20Duties%20expected%20from%20its%20citizens%2C%20including%20fostering%20a%20spirit%20of%20common%20brotherhood%2C%20striving%20for%20excellence%2C%20and%20preserving%20the%20natural%20environment.%20These%20principles%20align%20closely%20with%20Hinduism's%20ethos%20of%20tolerance%2C%20harmony%2C%20and%20a%20shared%20sense%20of%20brotherhood%20transcending%20religious%2C%20linguistic%2C%20and%20regional%20diversities.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20core%20value%20of%20fraternity%20enshrined%20in%20the%20Preamble%20of%20the%20Constitution%20is%20directly%20borrowed%20from%20the%20Hindu%20Upanishadic%20ideal%20of%20%3Cem%3E'Vasudhaiva%20Kutumbakam%2C'%20%3C%2Fem%3Ewhich%20means%20%26quot%3Bthe%20whole%20world%20is%20one%20family.%26quot%3B%20This%20inclusion%20in%20the%20Constitution%20subtly%20acknowledges%20that%20the%20essence%20of%20Indian%20culture%20is%20fundamentally%20Hindu%20but%20inherently%20inclusive%2C%20respecting%20and%20tolerating%20all%20other%20faiths.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHinduism%20has%20a%20strong%20tradition%20of%20coexistence%20with%20nature.%20Article%2051-A(g)%20of%20the%20Constitution%20emphasizes%20the%20duty%20of%20every%20citizen%20to%20protect%20and%20improve%20the%20natural%20environment%2C%20including%20forests%2C%20lakes%2C%20rivers%2C%20wildlife%2C%20and%20to%20have%20compassion%20for%20living%20creatures.%20This%20reflects%20the%20%3Cem%3ESanatani%3C%2Fem%3E%20way%20of%20life%2C%20which%20not%20only%20respects%20human%20beings%20but%20also%20extends%20this%20respect%20to%20animals%20and%20the%20environment.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECow%20Protection%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHinduism's%20reverence%20for%20the%20cow%20is%20deeply%20ingrained%20in%20the%20Indian%20Sanatani%20society.%20Article%2048%20of%20the%20Constitution%20directs%20the%20state%20to%20organise%20agriculture%20and%20animal%20husbandry%20on%20modern%20and%20scientific%20lines%2C%20emphasizing%20the%20preservation%20and%20improvement%20of%20cow%20breeds%20and%20prohibiting%20the%20slaughter%20of%20cows%20and%20calves.%20This%20also%20aligns%20with%20Mahatma%20Gandhi's%20ideals%20and%20enforces%20the%20importance%20of%20protecting%20cows%20through%20legislation.%20It%20is%20worth%20noting%20that%20Gandhi%20was%20always%20proud%20of%20being%20a%20Sanatani%20Hindu.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESanskrit%20and%20Hindi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESanskrit%2C%20the%20language%20of%20Hindu%20scriptures%2C%20plays%20a%20unifying%20role%20in%20Hinduism.%20Articles%20343%20and%20351%20of%20the%20Indian%20Constitution%20makes%20Hindi%20the%20official%20language%20of%20the%20Union%3B%20encouraging%20its%20use%20with%20a%20primary%20basis%20in%20Sanskrit%20vocabulary.%20This%20promotes%20the%20spread%20of%20Hindi%20as%20a%20unifying%20language.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Indian%20Constitution's%20foundation%20is%20deeply%20rooted%20in%20Sanatan%2C%20which%20is%20not%20just%20a%20religion%20but%20a%20way%20of%20life%20encompassing%20humanism%20and%20humanity.%20Hindu%20cultural%20and%20philosophical%20principles%20have%20significantly%20contributed%20to%20the%20core%20values%20and%20structure%20of%20India's%20governance%2C%20reinforcing%20the%20idea%20that%20India's%20diverse%20tapestry%20is%20bound%20together%20by%20the%20threads%20of%20its%20ancient%20heritage.%20Sanatan%20is%20the%20basic%20structure%20and%20quintessence%20of%20the%20Indian%20Constitution.%3C%2F