hi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20Canadian%20government%20has%20both%20human%20and%20signal%20intelligence%20involving%20Indian%20officials%2C%20including%20diplomats%20posted%20in%20Canada%2C%20to%20link%20them%20to%20the%20death%20of%20Hardeep%20Singh%20Nijjar%2C%20according%20to%20Canadian%20media%20reports.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cbc.ca%2Fnews%2Fpolitics%2Fsikh-nijjar-india-canada-trudeau-modi-1.6974607%5C%22%3EThe%20public%20broadcaster%20CBC%3C%2Fa%3E%20quoted%20government%20sources%20as%20stating%20that%20based%20on%20a%20month-long%20investigation%20into%20Nijjar%E2%80%99s%20death%2C%20the%20Canadian%20government%20had%20amassed%20both%20%E2%80%9Chuman%20and%20signals%20intelligence%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThat%20intelligence%20includes%20communications%20involving%20Indian%20officials%20themselves%2C%20including%20Indian%20diplomats%20present%20in%20Canada%2C%20say%20Canadian%20government%20sources%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20article%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ECBC%20further%20claimed%20that%20some%20of%20the%20intelligence%20was%20%E2%80%9Cprovided%20by%20an%20unnamed%20ally%20in%20the%20Five%20Eyes%20intelligence%20alliance%E2%80%9D.%20The%20Five%20Eyes%20intelligence%20sharing%20network%20consists%20of%20the%20US%2C%20the%20UK%2C%20Australia%2C%20Canada%20and%20New%20Zealand.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20news%20agency%20Associated%20Press%2C%20following%20up%20on%20the%20CBC%20report%2C%20said%20an%20unnamed%20Canadian%20official%20revealed%20similar%20details%20to%20it.%20The%20official%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapnews.com%2Farticle%2Findia-canada-visas-sikh-activist-killing-381e973e84f8d0c10b0bd53b03ccbdf2%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20allegations%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9Cinvolvement%20in%20the%20killing%20of%20a%20Sikh%20Canadian%20is%20based%20on%20surveillance%20of%20Indian%20diplomats%20in%20Canada%2C%20including%20intelligence%20provided%20by%20a%20major%20ally%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20added%20that%20Canadian%20officials%20went%20to%20India%20on%20several%20occasions%20%E2%80%9Cseeking%20cooperation%20in%20the%20investigation%E2%80%9D%2C%20with%20Canada%E2%80%99s%20National%20Security%20and%20Intelligence%20Adviser%20Jody%20Thomas%20staying%20in%20India%20for%20four%20days%20in%20mid-August%2C%20then%20again%20for%20five%20days%20this%20month%20during%20the%20G-20%20summit.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Canadian%20prime%20minister%20had%20raised%20the%20matter%20of%20Nijjar%E2%80%99s%20killing%20during%20his%20short%20and%20tense%20meeting%20with%20PM%20Narendra%20Modi%20on%20the%20last%20day%20of%20the%20G-20%20summit%20on%20September%2010.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CCanadian%20sources%20say%20that%2C%20when%20pressed%20behind%20closed%20doors%2C%20no%20Indian%20official%20has%20denied%20the%20bombshell%20allegation%20at%20the%20core%20of%20this%20case%C2%A0%E2%80%94%20that%20there%20is%20evidence%20to%20suggest%20Indian%20government%20involvement%20in%20the%20assassination%20of%20a%20Canadian%20citizen%C2%A0on%20Canadian%20soil%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20the%20CBC%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOn%20Monday%2C%20Prime%20Minister%20Justin%20Trudeau%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fcanada-accuses-indian-government-of-assassinating-sikh-citizen-in-vancouver-expels-senior-diplomat%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Parliament%20that%20Canadian%20agencies%20were%20%E2%80%9Cactively%20pursuing%20credible%20allegations%20of%20a%20potential%20link%20between%20agents%20of%20the%20Government%20of%20India%20and%20the%20killing%20of%20a%20Canadian%20citizen%2C%20Hardeep%20Singh%20Nijjar%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENijjar%2C%20who%20became%20a%20Canadian%20citizen%20in%202007%2C%20is%20described%20by%20India%20as%20a%20pro-Khalistani%20terrorist.%20He%20was%20shot%20dead%20outside%20a%20gurudwara%20in%20Surrey%20on%20June%2018.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIndia%20immediately%20dismissed%20the%20allegations%20as%20%E2%80%9Cmotivated%20and%20absurd%E2%80%9D.%20It%20also%20announced%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Findia-canada-visa-suspension%5C%22%3Esuspension%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20visa%20operations%20in%20all%20its%20missions%20in%20Canada.%20The%20Canadian%20high%20commission%20also%20said%20that%20it%20would%20send%20back%20staff%20due%20to%20security%20threats%20on%20social%20media%2C%20but%20India%20claimed%20that%20it%20was%20being%20done%20due%20to%20New%20Delhi%20seeking%20mutual%20parity%20on%20diplomatic%20representation.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Ministry%20of%20External%20Affairs%20spokesperson%20also%20told%20reporters%20that%20New%20Delhi%20has%20told%20Ottawa%20that%20it%20was%20%E2%80%9Cwilling%20to%20look%20at%20any%20specific%20information%20that%20is%20provided%20to%20us%E2%80%9D.%20%E2%80%9CBut%20so%20far%20we%20have%20not%20received%20any%20such%20specific%20information%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said%20on%20Thursday%20afternoon%20in%20New%20Delhi.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20had%20also%20dubbed%20Canada%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiatoday.in%2Findia%2Fstory%2Fsafe-havens-provided-abroad-including-canada-india-on-terror-activities-2438652-2023-09-21%5C%22%3Esafe%20haven%20for%20terrorists%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%2C%20a%20term%20that%20was%20only%20used%20for%20Pakistan%20so%20far.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20in%20New%20York%20on%20Thursday%2C%20Trudeau%20reiterated%20the%20allegations%20and%20suggested%20that%20the%20evidence%20would%20emerge%20from%20an%20eventual%20legal%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20an%20independent%20justice%20system%20and%20robust%20processes%20that%20will%20follow%20their%20course%20and%20we%20call%20upon%20the%20Government%20of%20India%20to%20engage%20with%20us%20to%20move%20forward%20on%20getting%20to%20the%20truth%20of%20this%20matter%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fcanadian-pm-justin-trudeau-reiterates-allegations-of-indias-role-in-sikh-leaders-murder%5C%22%3Ehe%20said%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20sidelines%20of%20the%20UN%20general%20assembly.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ETrudeau%20said%20that%20the%20decision%20to%20share%20these%20allegations%20%E2%80%9Cwas%20not%20done%20lightly%E2%80%9D%20but%20%E2%80%9Cwith%20the%20utmost%20seriousness%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20UK%20newspaper%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ft.com%2Fcontent%2F54721d57-fe1b-4d28-ab9b-a664f110770b%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EFinancial%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported%20that%20US%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20and%20other%20Western%20leaders%20had%20%E2%80%9Cexpressed%20concern%E2%80%9D%20about%20Canada%E2%80%99s%20allegation%20that%20Indian%20government%20officials%20were%20involved%20in%20Nijjar%E2%80%99s%20killing.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThree%20people%20familiar%20with%20the%20discussions%20at%20the%20summit%20said%20several%20members%20of%20the%20Five%20Eyes%E2%80%A6%20raised%20the%20killing%20of%20Hardeep%20Singh%20Nijjar%20with%20Modi.%20One%20said%20Biden%20felt%20it%20was%20important%20to%20address%20the%20issue%20directly%20with%20his%20Indian%20counterpart%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Cem%3EFT%3C%2Fem%3E%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhite%20House%20backs%20Canada%2C%20no%20direct%20condemnation%20of%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThere%20was%20no%20clarity%20from%20The%20White%20House%20on%20whether%20Biden%20had%20raised%20the%20matter%20directly.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20US%20national%20security%20advisor%20Jake%20Sullivan%20came%20out%20strongly%20to%20back%20Canada%2C%20but%20again%20without%20directly%20condemning%20India.%20He%20said%20that%20he%20had%20%E2%80%9Cseen%20in%20the%20press%20some%20efforts%20to%20try%20to%20drive%20a%20wedge%20between%20the%20United%20States%20and%20Canada%20on%20this%20issue%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farchive.li%2FSu1XC%5C%22%3EA%3Cem%3E%20Washington%20Post%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20report%20had%20earlier%20claimed%20that%20some%20of%20the%20Five%20Eyes%20countries%2C%20including%20the%20US%2C%20had%20rebuffed%20the%20proposal%20by%20Canada%20to%20issue%20a%20joint%20statement%20condemning%20India.%20This%20article%20was%20widely%20picked%20up%20in%20the%20Indian%20and%20Canadian%20media%20as%20a%20sign%20that%20the%20US%20was%20not%20supporting%20its%20northern%20neighbour.%20While%20the%20Canadian%20government%20had%20denied%20that%20any%20such%20proposal%20was%20made%2C%20a%20US%20NSC%20spokesperson%20later%20strongly%20dismissed%20the%20report%20on%20Wednesday%20as%20%E2%80%9Cfalse%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20deep%20concerns%20about%20the%20allegations%2C%20and%20we%20would%20like%20to%20see%20this%20investigation%20carried%20forward%20and%20the%20perpetrators%20held%20to%20account.%20That%20is%20what%20the%20United%20States%20has%20stood%20for%20from%20the%20moment%20this%20emerged%20in%20public%2C%20and%20we%20will%20continue%20to%20stand%20for%20that%20until%20this%20fully%20plays%20its%20way%20out%2C%E2%80%9D%20Sullivan%20said%20in%20a%20White%20House%20briefing%20on%20Thursday%20in%20Washington.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.whitehouse.gov%2Fbriefing-room%2Fpress-briefings%2F2023%2F09%2F21%2Fpress-briefing-by-press-secretary-karine-jean-pierre-and-national-security-advisor-jake-sullivan-8%2F%5C%22%3EWhen%20asked%3C%2Fa%3E%20whether%20the%20US%20had%20any%20evidence%20to%20support%20Canadian%20claims%2C%20Sullivan%20demurred.%20%C2%A0%E2%80%9CI%E2%80%99m%20not%20going%20to%20speak%20to%20either%20intelligence%20or%20law%20enforcement%20matters%20from%20this%20podium.%20I%20will%20let%20that%20process%20play%20out.%20We%20are%20in%2C%20as%20I%20said%20before%2C%20continuous%20communication%20and%20consultation%20with%20the%20Canadian%20government.%20And%20we%20will%20remain%20so%20as%20we%20go%20forward%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20added%20that%20the%20US%20has%20also%20%E2%80%9Cbeen%20and%20will%20be%20in%20contact%20with%20the%20Indians%20at%20high%20levels%20on%20this%20issue%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBoth%20Washington%20and%20Canberra%20have%20asked%20India%20to%20join%20the%20investigation.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20he%20didn%E2%80%99t%20condemn%20India%2C%20Sullivan%20reiterated%20that%20the%20White%20House%20was%20taking%20the%20allegation%20%E2%80%9Cseriously%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%E2%80%99s%20something%20we%20will%20keep%20working%20on%2C%20and%20we%20will%20do%20that%20regardless%20of%20the%20country.%20There%20is%20not%20some%20special%20exemption%20you%20get%20for%20actions%20like%20this.%20Regardless%20of%20the%20country%2C%20we%20will%20stand%20up%20and%20defend%20our%20basic%20principles.%C2%A0%20And%20we%20will%20also%20consult%20closely%20with%20allies%20like%20Canada%20as%20they%20pursue%20their%20law%20enforcement%20and%20diplomatic%20process%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695363831000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F22114805%2FScreenshot-2023-09-22-at-11.46.58-AM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fcanada-communications-indian-diplomats-nijjar-killing-probe%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%E2%80%9CCanadian%20sources%20say%20that%2C%20when%20pressed%20behind%20closed%20doors%2C%20no%20Indian%20official%20has%20denied%20the%20bombshell%20allegation%20at%20the%20core%20of%20this%20case%C2%A0%E2%80%94%20that%20there%20is%20evidence%20to%20suggest%20Indian%20government%20involvement%20in%20the%20assassination%20of%20a%20Canadian%20citizen%C2%A0on%20Canadian%20soil%2C%E2%80%9D%20public%20broadcaster%20CBC%20reported.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fcanada-communications-indian-diplomats-nijjar-killing-probe%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Resignations%20have%20no%20impact%20on%20expansion%2C%20more%20pilots%20joining%3A%20Akasa%20CEO%22%2C%22c