is%20exempted%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20read.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESources%20within%20the%20administration%20say%20that%20no%20progress%20has%20been%20made%20in%20investigating%20Lalit%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20cases%20%E2%80%93%20both%20the%20one%20in%20which%20the%20the%20Tamil%20Nadu%20government%20requested%20a%20CBI%20investigation%20and%20the%20PMLA%20case%20registered%20by%20the%20ED%2C%20in%20which%20the%20court%20had%20permitted%20ED%20to%20seek%20extradition.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESince%20there%20is%20no%20investigation%20against%20Lalit%20Modi%2C%20no%20charge%20sheet%20can%20be%20filed%2C%20and%20therefore%2C%20a%20request%20for%20extradition%20or%20RCN%20would%20not%20succeed.%20Thus%2C%20it%20appears%20that%20little%20has%20been%20done%20to%20address%20INTERPOL%E2%80%99s%20main%20ground%20for%20rejection%20of%20an%20RCN%20against%20Modi%20%E2%80%93%20%E2%80%9Cinsufficient%20judicial%20data%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EGovernment%E2%80%99s%20attitude%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Narendra%20Modi%20government%E2%80%99s%20long%20delay%20in%20deciding%20upon%20this%20request%20for%20a%20CBI%20probe%20against%20Lalit%20Modi%20is%20unusual%20since%20investigating%20agencies%20like%20the%20CBI%20and%20ED%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20under%20the%20present%20regime%2C%20have%20been%20quick%20to%20file%20cases%2C%20summon%20for%20interrogation%2C%20and%20arrest%20or%20detain%20several%20political%20leaders%20in%20the%20opposition%20camps.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20March%202011%2C%20the%20then%20Congress%20government%20had%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Fpolitics-and-nation%2Fgovt-revokes-lalit-modis-passport%2Farticleshow%2F7628666.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Erevoked%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Lalit%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20Indian%20passport%20under%20Section%2010(3)(C)%20of%20The%20Passport%20Act%2C%201967.%20According%20to%20this%20section%2C%20the%20government%20may%20order%20impounding%20%E2%80%9Cif%20the%20passport%20authority%20deems%20it%20necessary%20to%20do%20so%20in%20the%20interest%20of%20the%20sovereignty%20and%20integrity%20of%20India%2C%20the%20security%20of%20India%2C%20friendly%20relations%20of%20India%20with%20any%20foreign%20country%2C%20or%20in%20the%20interest%20of%20the%20general%20public.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20August%202014%2C%20the%20Delhi%20high%20court%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapnews.com%2Fcourt-orders-lalit-modis-passport-to-be-restored-c65bc0e63fce4f7189a001b7c39b7dc6%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Erestored%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20passport%20saying%20it%20was%20%E2%80%9Cwrongly%20revoked%E2%80%9D%20and%20that%20ED%E2%80%99s%20case%20was%20moving%20too%20slowly%20and%20lacked%20substantial%20evidence.%20The%20government%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Flalit-modi-one-of-four-passport-cases-govt-didnt-challenge%2Farticleshow%2F48196248.cms%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Edid%20not%20challenge%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20order.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%202015%2C%20reports%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fworld-asia-india-33130436%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Enoted%20how%20Keith%20Vaz%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20a%20Labour%20Party%20member%20of%20parliament%20in%20the%20United%20Kingdom%20used%20the%20name%20of%20the%20then%20external%20affairs%20minister%20of%20India%2C%20the%20late%20Sushma%20Swaraj%2C%20to%20exert%20influence%20on%20senior%20immigration%20officials%2C%20urging%20them%20to%20expedite%20the%20processing%20of%20British%20travel%20documents%20for%20Lalit%20Modi%20during%20a%20time%20before%20the%20court%20order%20came%20in%202014%2C%20when%20his%20passport%20was%20still%20revoked.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBoth%20Lalit%20Modi%20and%20Sushma%20Swaraj%20acknowledged%20the%20truth%20of%20these%20revelations%20but%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Findia%2Fpolitics%2Fafter-sunday-times-report-sushma-says-she-backed-lalit-modi-travel-documents-on-humanitarian-grounds%2F%23sthash.tfJFTmzc.dpuf%5C%22%3Edefended%3C%2Fa%3E%20their%20actions%20as%20purely%20driven%20by%20humanitarian%20considerations.%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20wife%20was%20in%20Portugal%20and%20was%20suffering%20from%20cancer.%20%3Cspan%3ESubsequently%2C%20Modi%20was%20granted%20permission%20to%20visit%20his%20wife%20on%20multiple%20occasions.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELalit%20Modi%20was%20also%20thought%20to%20be%20close%20to%20BJP%20leader%20and%20former%20chief%20minister%20of%20Rajasthan%2C%20Vasundhara%20Raje.%20During%20her%20initial%20term%20as%20CM%20from%202003%20to%202008%2C%20he%20gained%20substantial%20prominence%20in%20Rajasthan%20and%20was%20often%20referred%20to%20as%20the%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.telegraphindia.com%2Findia%2Fa-cm-and-her-super-cm%2Fcid%2F1511931%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Esuper%20chief%20minister%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELalit%20Modi%20was%20one%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98Modis%E2%80%99%20referred%20to%20by%20Congress%20leader%20Rahul%20Gandhi%20in%20his%202019%20election%20campaign%20speech%20at%20Kolar%20in%20Karnataka.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20defamation%20case%20filed%20against%20Gandhi%20led%20to%20a%20conviction%20this%20year%2C%20along%20with%20a%20two-year%20sentence%20that%20led%20to%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20suspension%20from%20parliament.%20The%20Supreme%20Court%20later%20stayed%20the%20sentence%20and%20his%20membership%20of%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20was%20restored.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ESaurav%20Das%20is%20an%20independent%20investigative%20journalist%20and%20tweets%20%40%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EOfficialSauravD.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%